    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-01-22T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-22T16:00:00-05:00" n="389"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d389">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/1–2252: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 389<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Chairman of the United States Delegation at the
                        United Nations General Assembly (<persName corresp="#p_RE1" type="from"
                            >Roosevelt</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-01-22T22:00:00+01:00"
                            >January 22, 1952—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 1142. For Hickerson (<gloss
                        target="#t_UNA1">UNA</gloss>) from Gross. Re: Suez. <persName
                        corresp="#p_EAS1">Eban</persName> (Israel) on instrs from Tel Aviv said his
                    govt is increasingly restless <pb facs="0924" n="884" xml:id="pg_884"/> about
                    inactivity <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> on Suez res.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d389fn1">Reference is to the resolution adopted by the Security
                        Council on Sept. 1, 1951 calling upon Egypt to terminate restrictions on the
                        passage of international shipping through the Suez Canal (U.N. doc. S/2322);
                        for text, see <ref target="frus1951v05#pg_848">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1951, vol. V, p.
                        848</ref>.</note> It fears world attention re Suez is focused so much on
                    Anglo-Egypt relations that Israel’s interests in unmolested transit is becoming
                    forgotten. <persName corresp="#p_EAS1">Eban</persName> has talked along same
                    line to <persName corresp="#p_JSH1">Jebb</persName>. I gather this is first
                    warning of possible Israeli plan to present at Suez ports cargoes or ships
                    openly destined for Israel. If transit refused, Israel would probably raise
                    matter in <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>, seeking <gloss target="#t_SC1"
                        >SC</gloss> steps to obtain compliance with Sept 1 <gloss target="#t_SC1"
                        >SC</gloss> res.</p>
                <p>Does Dept want me to talk with <persName corresp="#p_JSH1">Jebb</persName>, and
                    if so along what line?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
